From ab6011a841e002a6ce8d17ba78933c8b244aafda Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 21:21:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Browse page for exploring media by tag, genre, and
 channel

Uses the new Tunarr Scheduler browse endpoints:
- GET /api/tags, /api/tags/:tag/media
- GET /api/genres, /api/genres/:genre/media
- GET /api/catalog/channels, /api/catalog/channels/:channel-name/media

Changes:
- New Browse page with Tags / Genres / Channels facet tabs, a filter
  input, and per-facet entry lists (tag usage counts + example titles,
  channel descriptions). Selecting an entry shows its media with
  client-side pagination; tag/genre chips on results cross-link to
  browsing by that value.
- /browse routes with pushState/deep-link support
  (/browse/:facet and /browse/:facet/:selection).
- Tags, genres, and channels chips on the media detail page are now
  clickable and jump to the Browse page.
- Card components pass through props besides :class (e.g. :on-click).
- Scheduler media items arrive with namespaced JSON keys; they're
  normalized (namespace stripped) on receipt.

